.method public hidebysig newslot virtual instance string GetFreeBusy([in]valuetype System.DateTime Start, [in]int32 MinPerChar, [in]object CompleteFormat) runtime managed
Public Function GetFreeBusy (Start As DateTime, MinPerChar As Integer, Optional CompleteFormat As Object) As String

Docs.param: The date of availability, starting at midnight.
Specifies the length of each time slot in minutes. Default is 30 minutes.

A value of True indicates that a finer granularity of busy time is returned in the free/busy string. A value of False indicates that a distinction between only the available and busy times is returned.
Docs.summary: Obtains a String (string in C#) representing the availability of the for a period of 30 days from the start date, beginning at midnight of the date specified.
Docs.returns: A String (string in C#) that represents the availability of the Exchange user for a period of 30 days from the start date, beginning at midnight of the date specified. Each character in the String (string in C#) is a value indicating if the user is available (0), and optionally, whether a busy time is marked tentative (1), out of office (3), or other (2).

MemberSignature.Value: .method public hidebysig newslot virtual instance class stdole.StdPicture GetPicture() runtime managed

Docs.summary: Obtains a object that represents the picture of the Microsoft Exchange user that is displayed in Microsoft Outlook.

remarks.para: The picture of the Exchange user is stored in Active Directory and displayed in various places in Outlook, including the dialog box for Outlook Properties and Contact Card.If the picture does not exist for the user, GetPicture returns Nothing (a null reference (Nothing in Visual Basic) in C#).

You can only call GetPicture from code that runs in-process as Outlook. An StdPicture object cannot be marshaled across process boundaries. If you attempt to call GetPicture from out-of-process code, an exception occurs.
